The dynamictasklist does not seem to support wiki markup - which makes it much less useful that it would be if it _did_ support wiki markup.

Even better, would be if users could define their own lists - i.e. define columns etc - and then sort and filter them, with each cell in the list potentially containing wiki markup.  Almost like including a (very small) subset of Excel in Confluence.  (I understand JotSpot does something along these lines, but I don't know the details.)

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
