The ">" (&gt;) in the Breadcrumbs are partly hardcoded. Many of them can be changed by updating tons of templates, but one is hardcoded in com.atlassian.confluence.pages.actions.AbstractPageAction - I cannot change that.
A centralized option for that would be great. I'd like to have an image instead of ">"...

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-3468].
  {panel}

When you write a headline in confluence (i.e.: "h2. Foo") the result contains a link, actually an anchor (<h2><a name="Foo">Foo</a><h2>). Is there any way to get around of that? The styles get confused and in FireFox the result is quite ugly (in my case: jumping from normal to bold).
I'd like to get rid of that, at least not surrounding my headlines... (i.e. <a name="Foo"></a><h2>Foo<h2>)

