When I saw the "Import pages from disk" action, I thought of how this might make it easier for us to import information into Confluence.  However, most of the directories I could think of have a mix of documents, presentations, PDFs, or text files. Importing a directory with a mix of these is not useful.  It would be great if the import could be made more intelligent by creating pages for certain extensions (txt) and allowing other extensions (doc, pdf, prs, xls, ...) to be imported as attachments.  What page would the attachments belong to?  Perhaps all on the same page named after the directory it came from? Perhaps a user specified page? Perhaps each attachment is its own page with the name taken from the file like the current support?  The last option is probably the most flexible and easier to start with.

